{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"All direct and transitive dependencies are extracted from the manifest and included in the vulnerability check.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is the handoff between dependency extraction/resolution and vulnerability-check input construction. A unit test of only parsing can miss dropped transitive deps during wiring.","test_description":"Run scanner dependency-discovery against fixture projects (e.g., npm with lockfile, pip with pinned transitive set) and assert the assembled vulnerability-check request set contains both direct and transitive packages with versions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The vulnerability database query returns results that match the exact version ranges in the manifest, not just the package name.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Real failures often come from API contract details (range syntax, inclusive/exclusive bounds, normalization) that mocks may not replicate. Minimum reliable boundary is real HTTP interaction with the actual vuln API (or a true contract-equivalent service).","test_description":"Execute scanner against a test manifest with carefully chosen version ranges and perform a real API query path; assert returned CVEs correspond only to vulnerable versions in-range and exclude out-of-range CVEs for the same package.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.72,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The severity sorting places Critical above High above Medium above Low, with CVEs of the same severity sorted by CVSS score.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is deterministic sorting logic in one function/object boundary with no required I/O or cross-module state propagation.","test_description":"Provide unsorted CVE fixtures covering all severities and equal-severity mixed CVSS values; assert exact output order: severity rank first, then CVSS descending within each severity.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.92,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The manifest modification changes only the affected dependency's version, leaving all other entries unchanged.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real regressions occur at parse-modify-serialize boundaries (key ordering, formatting, accidental edits to unrelated fields). Unit-testing only the patch function can miss serializer side effects.","test_description":"Apply update flow to real manifest files on disk, then diff original vs updated content/AST and assert exactly one dependency version changed and all other dependency entries remain identical.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The auto-generated pull request is created on the real repository with the correct single-dependency diff.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This behavior depends on real VCS/remote repository interactions and API behavior. Mocked PR clients can hide auth, branch, diff, and server-side validation failures.","test_description":"Run end-to-end PR creation against a real test repository, then verify PR exists remotely and changed files/diff show only the intended dependency bump.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.88,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"A major version bump is correctly identified as a breaking change based on semver comparison.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Semver major-bump detection is deterministic local logic and does not require module orchestration or I/O to expose the core failure.","test_description":"Test semver comparison function with representative pairs (including pre-release/build metadata edge cases) and assert breaking-change flag is true only when major version increases per semver rules.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.94,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When a breaking change is detected, PR creation is skipped and a review flag is surfaced in the scanner output.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This checks orchestration across decision logic, PR-creation boundary, and reporting output. A single-function unit test can miss side-effect suppression wiring.","test_description":"Run scanner pipeline with an input that triggers major bump; assert PR client is not invoked and scanner output contains the expected review-required flag/reason.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}}]}
